        <title>What Does This Mean for You? How Can This Process Help You in Your Own Teaching?</title>
        <contents>&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/teacher_and_students.png" width="176" height="338" alt="Teacher working with students" style="margin: 5px 15px; float: right;" /&gt;Helps &lt;em&gt;identify areas of focus.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Helps &lt;em&gt;determine potential difficulties&lt;/em&gt; for learners.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Helps &lt;em&gt;prioritize instruction&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Allows you to &lt;em&gt;notice the academic language&lt;/em&gt; found in the texts you use.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_MOD1_UNIT2_0130.mp3"&gt;ELL_MOD1_UNIT2_0130.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;That is a lot to think about. Because this is not a course in linguistics, let’s focus on what you can do for starters to decide what makes a text difficult for a learner and then think about what you might choose to focus on in instruction. For example, in the lesson on personality and the birth-order theory, the teacher decided to focus on text structure and find main ideas and details to support the claim in the reading. The teacher also worked on connotations and the pronunciation of vocabulary related to the personality traits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
