        <title>Some Additional Resources</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;If you would like to learn more about helping ELLs with complex texts and structures, read Fillmore and Fillmore (2011), &lt;a target="_blank" title="What does text complexity mean for English learners and language minority students?" href="http://ell.stanford.edu/publication/what-does-text-complexity-mean-english-learners-and-language-minority-students"&gt;&lt;em&gt;What Does Text Complexity Mean for English Language Learners and Minority Students?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Even though for K–12 educators, it has many relevant ideas, especially for those working in adult secondary education.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Be sure to visit &lt;a title="Understanding Language" href="http://ell.stanford.edu/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Understanding Language&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; at Stanford University for research, resources, and sample lessons for teaching academic language.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
